blog.description: mari, 23 • i'm in love with jikook • asks | ao3

summary: This sounds weird but lately I’ve been thinking about where does BTS go from here. Like they’re absolutely killing it, killing...
question: This sounds weird but lately I’ve been thinking about where does BTS go from here. Like they’re absolutely killing it, killing me. And I honestly cant even think about a next comeback or what they're gonna do next - songs/concepts/visuals/topics. Its like they’re already above the top level & I dont know they even top themselves again and again. I really cant imagine anything for the future, its crazy
answer:
It is crazy, they’re incredible. I sometimes think the same because I’m always so overwhelmed with the quality of their work, from the lyrics, concepts, melodies, beats, videos, everything.
But at the same time I know that music is dynamic and if there’s something I’ve learned from watching them through the years, it’s that they’re not afraid to try different styles and that they’re passionate about their work. It’s one of things that made me fall in love with them in the first place. 

No matter how successful you are and no matter how much you achieve, I feel that if you’re passionate about what you do and if it gives you happiness (for you), you’d keep doing it forever. If it’s to compete, to feel superior or for other reasons that don’t involve your growth as a person then after reaching a certain height, there’s no point, or it’s very insignificant. 

If they’re as passionate as they seem and if this gives them happiness, I believe that they’ll do more and more. They’re 7 amazing and different people that lean on each other and work together, the possibilities are endless. I hope we’ll be able to watch them for a long time. ♡
